{
  "answer": "**The speaker claims that his sole occupation, or the entirety of his life, is playing the game of love.**[^1]\n\nThis is the opening couplet of the ghazal, where the poet Zauq declares: \"My life is this: the game of love I play. / What is real, and what's the fleeting way?\" The phrase \"shughl-e-ishq-baazi\" from the title and first line directly translates to \"the occupation [or pastime] of love-play,\" establishing love as his defining pursuit.[^1]\n\n[^1]: Sheikh Ibrahim Zauq, *Diwan-E-Zauq*, [paragraph](/works/sheikh-ibrahim-zauq-diwan-e-zauq-0fa798/20-hum-hain-aur-shughl-e-ishq-baazi-hai/translation/#p-f826e7).",
